Private Sub Report_Open(Cancel As Integer)
  Dim promptmsg As String
  Dim Instrg As String
  On Error GoTo SubError ' <-- goes to bottome of the Sub and displays message
  ' <- tick mark means comment  Add these anywhere
  ' Fill in the first part of the report Title
  Me.rptTitle.Caption = "Judges Summary Report. "
  ' Build a string to put in the inputbox as a prompt to user
  '  Stings are in quotes unless you use a string variable or constant
  '  promptmsg is a string variable,
  '  Note to continue on next line here, use the underscore character '_'
  '  the vbCrLf means go to a new line when the message is displayed
  '  the '&' character adds the strings together. you could use a + sign also
  promptmsg = "Enter STATUS Selection Criteria ---" & vbCrLf & _
     " * = ALL Judges {Default) " & vbCrLf & _
     " A = Active Judges Only (Status = A)" & vbCrLf & _
     " B = Blank: Non-Active Judges Only" & vbCrLf & _
     " I = Inactive: Judges Not Available this Year (Status=I)" & vbCrLf & _
     " E = EMail as Mail Preference" & vbCrLf & _
     " A Criteria -Examples: JCAT = 'SBEH' or NUM_YR = 3"
  Instrg = InputBox(promptmsg, "Judges Summary Report", "*")
  If Len(Instrg) = 0 Then Instrg = "*"
  If Len(Instrg) = 1 Then
   If UCase(Mid(Instrg, 1, 1)) = "*" Then
      Me.Filter = ""
      Me.rptTitle.Caption = Me.rptTitle.Caption & _
        "All Judges "
   End If
   If UCase(Mid(Instrg, 1, 1)) = "A" Then
      Me.Filter = "[STATUS] = 'A'"
      Me.rptTitle.Caption = Me.rptTitle.Caption & _
        "Active Judges "
   End If
   If UCase(Mid(Instrg, 1, 1)) = "I" Then
      Me.Filter = "[STATUS] = 'I'"
      Me.rptTitle.Caption = Me.rptTitle.Caption & _
        "Judges Registered as Inactive This Year"
   End If
   If UCase(Mid(Instrg, 1, 1)) = "E" Then
      Me.Filter = "[MAILPREF] = 'E'"
      Me.rptTitle.Caption = Me.rptTitle.Caption & _
        "Judges with e-Mail Pref "
   End If
   If UCase(Mid(Instrg, 1, 1)) = "B" Then
      Me.Filter = "[STATUS] = "" OR isnull([STATUS])"
      Me.rptTitle.Caption = Me.rptTitle.Caption & _
        "Non Active Judges (Status blank) "
   End If
  Else ' Len > 1 must be a string
     Me.Filter = Instrg
     Me.rptTitle.Caption = Me.rptTitle.Caption & _
       Instrg & " "
  End If
  Me.FilterOn = True
  promptmsg = "Enter Sort Order  --- " & vbCrLf & _
     " N = Judges [Name] (default)  OR ... " & vbCrLf & _
     " J = Judges Number [JUN] " & vbCrLf & _
     " Any of these field name(s) (comma separated): " & vbCrLf & _
     "   JUN, Name, STATUS, FIRST_YR, LAST_YR, NUM_YR, JCAT," & vbCrLf & _
     "   P_1, P_2, P_3, P_4, TEAM_OK "
  Instrg = InputBox(promptmsg, "Judges Summary Report", "N")
  If Len(Instrg) = 0 Then Instrg = "N"
  If Len(Instrg) = 1 Then
   If UCase(Mid(Instrg, 1, 1)) = "N" Then
      Me.OrderBy = "[NAME]"
      Me.rptTitle.Caption = Me.rptTitle.Caption & _
        "Sorted By Name "
   End If
   If UCase(Mid(Instrg, 1, 1)) = "J" Then
      Me.OrderBy = "[JUN]"
      Me.rptTitle.Caption = Me.rptTitle.Caption & _
       "Sorted By JUN "
   End If
  Else
     Me.OrderBy = Instrg
     Me.rptTitle.Caption = Me.rptTitle.Caption & _
       "Sorted by " & Instrg
  End If
  Me.OrderByOn = True
 
  
  Exit Sub
SubError:
  MsgBox (Err.Description)
End Sub
